last_episode_to_air.name: Off the Rails
last_episode_to_air.overview: The ladies of the Garden State reconvene for the first time to watch and react to the finale.

name: The Real Housewives of New Jersey
original_name: The Real Housewives of New Jersey
overview: We head to the Garden State for this installment of the “Housewives” franchise, focusing on affluent Jersey girls who are more than just friends. The cast has changed through the seasons but the featured housewives through the years have included Caroline Manzo, a devoted wife and mother of three adult children; former Las Vegas cosmetologist Jacqueline Laurita, who is now a full-time housewife; and Teresa Giudice, a mother of four who runs her household without help from a nanny or personal assistant.

seasons.name: Season 7
seasons.overview: Season 7 sees Teresa Giudice and Melissa Gorga joined by new Housewives Dolores Catania and Siggy Flicker, along with the return of a true Jersey veteran, Jacqueline Laurita. Also appearing this season are sisters Kathy Wakile and Rosie Pierri.

episodes.name: Thicker Than Water
episodes.overview: The lives of five affluent housewives - Teresa, Jacqueline, Caroline, Dina and Danielle - in New Jersey reveals a surprising twist: three of the housewives are related. Meanwhile, Caroline, who owns two businesses, prepares for her son's graduation party while mum-of-three Teresa plots her daughter Tia's road to stardom after watching her dancing.

episodes.name: Mamas Knows Best
episodes.overview: Danielle tries to warm to Dina but the women find themselves at a loss in each other's company, Jacqueline worries her daughter isn't getting good enough results at school while Teresa and daughter Gia receive good news about an audition. Meanwhile, Caroline's daughter concedes that she's ready to do her beauty course.

episodes.name: Not One of Us
episodes.overview: Danielle tries to bring tranquillity to the housewives' lives by organising a Moms' Night Out Spa Party but the mood turns sour when her guests circulate rumours. Later, Caroline and Dina pressure Jacqueline to end her friendship with Danielle.

episodes.name: Black & White and Read All Over
episodes.overview: Teresa is busy juggling her daughter's acting career and trying to move house. Meanwhile, the other housewives are busy discussing Danielle's alleged dodgy past, and Jacqueline decides to confront Danielle about the rumours which culminates in a showdown between Danielle and Teresa's husband.

episodes.name: Casinos and C-Cups
episodes.overview: Dina, Caroline and Teresa head to Atlantic City for a weekend of shopping, gambling and spa treatments. Teresa has an argument with her husband about plastic surgery after going bikini shopping, while Danielle is down in the dumps after splitting up with her boyfriend and turns to her children for support. Later, she pops out for a friendly birthday lunch with Jacqueline.

episodes.name: Finale
episodes.overview: Teresa's plans for a civilised dinner with the housewives and their families are scuppered when the ladies discuss Danielle's past. Danielle blames Dina for spreading rumours about her even when Caroline admits responsibility for gossiping about her, and an argument breaks out between the housewives and Teresa gets angry with her guests. Later, Teresa's husband tried to placate the guests with champagne.

episodes.name: The Last Supper
episodes.overview: There's more big hair and big drama with never-before-seen footage from the series as well as unseen footage from the housewives' dramatic reunion.

episodes.name: Reunion: Watch What Happens (1)
episodes.overview: Featuring a further look at previously unseen and explosive scenes from Teresa's dinner party. Battle lines are drawn and friendships on the line.

episodes.name: Reunion: Watch What Happens (2)
episodes.overview: Danielle's book is still at the forefront of the housewives' minds and the ladies chide her for bringing it to the dinner party. Later, Danielle asks whether she was the reason Jacqueline and Dina briefly stopped speaking to each other and both give her separate answers.

episodes.name: The Lost Footage
episodes.overview: This episode shows extended footage of the best fights and funniest moments from the series and offers more insight into the lives of the housewives.

episodes.name: Water Under The Table
episodes.overview: The birth of Jacqueline's baby boy brings the Manzo sisters even closer together and Danielle is still trying to make her way into their inner circle. Meanwhile, when Caroline throws her annual Sheriff's Fundraiser and doesn't invite Danielle, Danielle makes sure that everyone knows she was excluded.

episodes.name: Generation Vexed
episodes.overview: Jacqueline's daughter Ashley's behaviour continues to cause trouble for her mum. Meanwhile, Caroline does her best to stay out of her daughter's relationship problems, Teresa and Danielle's daughters are both invited to model in NYC Fashion Week, and Danielle extends an olive branch to her former friends to celebrate Christine's success.

episodes.name: Catty-Walk
episodes.overview: Danielle accuses Jacqueline of not being her own woman. Tired of all the negativity, Dina makes a date with a zen expert to purge Danielle from her life. Elsewhere, Teresa and Danielle's daughters model in Fashion Week, but mishaps on the catwalk could bring the future of their fashion careers into question.

episodes.name: Babies, Bubbles and Bubbies
episodes.overview: Teresa and Joe welcome their fourth child into the world. Meanwhile, Chris Manzo scores big when he gets an inside look into his dream business, Jacqueline gets a peek into her husband's secret safe, and Danielle gets an invitation she can't refuse but makes sure to get back-up from an old friend before she replies.

episodes.name: Into the Lion's Den
episodes.overview: Baby Audriana is home from the hospital and although Teresa and Joe couldn't be happier with their fourth child, Teresa pleads with Joe to get snipped. Meanwhile, Jacqueline and Ashley are still struggling to get along, but in true Manzo form, Caroline's kids try to bridge the gap.

episodes.name: It's Not Me, It's You
episodes.overview: After the outburst at The Brownstone, a battle breaks out on Facebook when Danielle accuses Jacqueline's teenage daughter of threatening her life. Wanting to put an end to the drama, Jacqueline and Teresa confront Ashley about the alleged attacks. Dina decides to follow her energist's advice and sets up a face-to-face meeting with Danielle to officially cut her out of her life.

episodes.name: Play At Your Own Risk
episodes.overview: Danielle, feeling empowered after standing up to the Manzo clan, decides it's time to live again. Jacqueline hosts a poker night with the guys and gets some scandalous information from Danielle's ex, Steve. Meanwhile, Dina can't deal with the constant fighting and makes a big decision that changes everything.

episodes.name: Bubbies Gone Bad
episodes.overview: Danielle goes under the knife to fix one of her biggest issues. Meanwhile, Teresa rolls out the red carpet for her long awaited housewarming party and Caroline deals with family issues.

episodes.name: Posche Spite
episodes.overview: Teresa and Jacqueline get an invitation they can't refuse, but worlds collide and tempers flare as they come face to face with Danielle.

episodes.name: Country Clubbed
episodes.overview: Teresa and Danielle face off at the Posche fashion show, the cops intervene, and the fight is retold from both sides.

episodes.name: Staub Wounds
episodes.overview: Jacqueline struggles to get Ashley to face the severity of her actions. Meanwhile, Albie grows anxious about his career as a lawyer.

episodes.name: Youth Will Be Served
episodes.overview: Teresa and Joe celebrate their 10-year anniversary in true Giudice style. Meanwhile, Ashley gets a surprise in the post that adds to her stress and Danielle tries to focus on the positive by planning her daughter Christine's Sweet 16. Will her ex-husband ruin the festivities?

episodes.name: Don't Drink the Holy Water
episodes.overview: Dina returns to fulfil her Godmother duties as Teresa and Joe spare no expense for baby Audriana's Christening. Elsewhere, Danielle discovers some disturbing news about one of her closest confidants.

episodes.name: The Chanels of Venice
episodes.overview: Teresa, Caroline and Jacqueline set sail on a cruise to Italy with their families, but the mix of three family generations can make for some rough waters. Back in Jersey and with the other wives away, Danielle slyly maneuvers onto enemy turf.

episodes.name: The Hills Are Alive With Giudice
episodes.overview: The Italy extravaganza continues as Teresa and Joe give everyone an all-out tour of their hometown, complete with hordes of relatives and a family dinner. Not to be outdone, Danielle meets with a private investigator in an effort to reconnect with her own family roots.

episodes.name: The Heads of Family Will Roll
episodes.overview: Teresa, Caroline, Jacqueline are back on Jersey's shores and are determined to put Danielle out of their lives for good. After an emotional dinner with her friends, Caroline confronts Danielle.

episodes.name: Reunion (1)
episodes.overview: Teresa Giudice, Caroline Manzo, Jacqueline Laurita and Danielle Staub reunite for the first part of the season two reunion special.

episodes.name: Reunion (2)
episodes.overview: Teresa Giudice, Caroline Manzo, Jacqueline Laurita and Danielle Staub reunite for the second part of the season two reunion special.

episodes.name: In The Name Of The Father
episodes.overview: Melissa and Kathy are busy preparing for a family christening. Jacqueline's lunch with Ashley goes sour when her feelings of guilt and frustration boil over, and Teresa focuses on saving her family from ruin.

episodes.name: Drop Dead Gorgas
episodes.overview: It's Halloween, and the aftermath of a christening gone awry leads to dramatic tricks and nary a treat. Meanwhile, the Brownstone hosts a fashion show. The catwalk sets the stage for catcalls and catfights, particularly when Kathy voices off and Caroline stands her ground.

episodes.name: Sealed With a Diss
episodes.overview: Jacqueline is haunted by her past as her relationship with her daughter continues to weaken. Meanwhile, life dramas impact Caroline's sons; Teresa attempts to reconcile with Melissa; and Kathy defends herself in a conversation with Caroline.

episodes.name: Gobblefellas
episodes.overview: The wives' Thanksgiving is stuffed with drama, resentment and regret. Divisions mark Turkey Day when Teresa presides over a "friendsgiving" feast for only Jacqueline, Caroline and their families. Conversely, the Gorgas host a separate get-together with the Wakiles.

episodes.name: Stick It
episodes.overview: Teresa encounters her brother for the first time since the tumultuous christening. Elsewhere, Melissa tries to fulfill her dream of being a pop star; Caroline plans to offer matronly advice on the radio; and Jacqueline's daughter plots to get a car.

episodes.name: Whine and Dine
episodes.overview: Caroline takes to the airwaves with her new radio show. Meanwhile, the Gorga siblings attempt to settle their differences, but they invariably stir up more tension; and Jacqueline plays referee in a face-off between Teresa and Melissa.

episodes.name: Teresa's Got a Gun
episodes.overview: Teresa and Melissa attempt to make peace, after which some of the gang journey to the Catskills. Back in the Garden State, Kathy savors the flavor of scouting for restaurants and Melissa prepares for a holiday dance recital. This spins into motion a family reunion---and it won't include Teresa.

episodes.name: Holidazed and Confused
episodes.overview: The holiday season looms in the Garden State, but it's not so merry when friction rises in Caroline's family. Meanwhile, Jacqueline throws a holiday bash. And Teresa and Joe try to add sizzle to their romantic life despite their financial troubles.

episodes.name: Twas the Fight Before Christmas
episodes.overview: The Jersey girls jingle all the way during Christmas, but it's much more naughty than nice when clashing and trashing mar Melissa's holiday party.

episodes.name: There Arose Such a Clatter
episodes.overview: The holiday season turns frosty when the Manzos tangle with Kim G. Meanwhile, Teresa and Kathy throw separate Christmas bashes; and Teresa isn't very merry in the wake of a decision.

episodes.name: A Very Jersey Christmas
episodes.overview: It's Christmas morning and housewives are stirring. Caroline receives a long-overdue present and Melissa considers herself the luckiest woman in Jersey. But there aren't many ho-ho-ho's for Teresa, whose holidays take a not-so-merry turn.

episodes.name: Auld Lang Syne for an Eye
episodes.overview: The wives get set to ring in the new year by trying fresh approaches to life: Teresa works on her new cookbooks; Melissa tries to live out her dream; and Caroline's daughter vows to shed pounds. The gang then celebrates New Year's Eve at the Brownstone, but backstabbing and finger-pointing prevail.

episodes.name: Child's Play No More
episodes.overview: Teresa's children have a play date with Melissa's children, yet the kids seemingly show more maturity than their parents. Meanwhile, Kathy mulls over how to nurture her teen daughter. And Ashley's father pays her a surprise visit, but there may be more going on than simply a family reunion.

episodes.name: Belly Up & Up
episodes.overview: Verbal warfare and an agonizing decision lowlight Jacqueline's relationship with her daughter. Meanwhile, Teresa's financial woes escalate. And the wives trek to Kathy's food-tasting bash, featuring surprise guests and unsavory behavior from Teresa and Melissa.

episodes.name: Black as Ink
episodes.overview: Caroline's pride spills over when her two sons set out to launch their bottled-water line. Meanwhile, Lauren's grand opening for her cosmetic venture brings Jacqueline together with her daughter; and Teresa's brother attends her book-signing event.

episodes.name: Singing in the Pain
episodes.overview: The wives are up and running when they participate in a charity race, with Teresa's competitive nature on full display. Meanwhile, Melissa premieres her song to an unforgiving crowd in Hoboken. And Teresa throws a birthday bash for one of her daughters, highlighted by a jaw-dropping gift.

episodes.name: Get to the Punta
episodes.overview: The Garden State ladies embark on a paradise getaway to Punta Cana in the Dominican Republic. Activities include a private cruise, but Kathy and Teresa soon make waves when they clash on the beach.

episodes.name: An Inconvenient Truce
episodes.overview: The wives continue their vacation in Punta Cana, but they discover the open-air market and streets can be hazardous (especially in heels). Back in the Garden State, Ashley considers getting a tattoo.

episodes.name: Portrait of an Italian Family
episodes.overview: Teresa and Melissa gather the family together for a photo; Kathy makes a shocking decision; Jacqueline and an unforeseen visitor work on mending family problems; and Teresa's new cookbook is released.

episodes.name: Reunion (1)
episodes.overview: The Garden State ladies reunite to hash out the dramas of Season 3

episodes.name: Reunion (2)
episodes.overview: The conclusion of a reunion featuring the Jersey girls trashing and clashing over Season 3's antics.

episodes.name: High Tide, Low Blow
episodes.overview: Caroline struggles to repair her friendship with Teresa and receives a diagnosis she feared. Jacqueline's daughter Ashley has spent more time than she should have at home, resulting in an ultimatum.

episodes.name: Poker Face
episodes.overview: Ashley has a hard time leaving the nest; Teresa's attempt at an apology turns into a violent brawl; Melissa has a musical surprise for Joe.

episodes.name: Third Eye Blind
episodes.overview: It's a gossip filled cruise down the Jersey coast; Jacqueline plays referee between two sisters-in-law.

episodes.name: Drowning Pool
episodes.overview: Caroline celebrates her anniversary; Kathy hosts a pool party; Teresa and Joe have a blow out; Jacqueline tries to deal with Ashley's new life.

episodes.name: Spoiled Sports
episodes.overview: Joe gives Teresa a shocking ultimatum; insecurities are revealed by Lauren when she talks with her dad about her weight loss; Jacqueline hosts a dramatic family field day.

episodes.name: Uncivil Union
episodes.overview: Jaime announces he will marry Rich; Caroline, Teresa, and Jacqueline come together but Joe makes a joke that goes too far; Kathy and Rosie have a heart-to-heart conversation.

episodes.name: True Love True Lies
episodes.overview: Caroline finds out what Teresa really thinks of her; Melissa debuts her new song with a party; Joe reaches out to his sister one last time.

episodes.name: Best Friends For Never
episodes.overview: Jacqueline's daughter, Ashley, is running out of options; Lauren makes a shocking decision regarding her weight loss; Teresa explores options with her bankruptcy attorney.

episodes.name: Public Displays of Rejection
episodes.overview: Teresa takes a big step with her brother; Melissa hosts a party for her radio debut; Teresa moves away from Jacqueline and Caroline.

episodes.name: Temporary Shrinkage
episodes.overview: Kathy tries to find love for her sister at the gay bar; Teresa and her brother, Joe discuss their issues in therapy; Jacqueline and Caroline discuss whether Teresa and her husband are still invited to the Napa trip; Rosie visits Teresa.

episodes.name: The Sniff Test
episodes.overview: Melissa oversees an overblown birthday bash for her daughter but an awkward meeting between Teresa and Jacqueline takes the cake. Meanwhile, Kathy serves up a meal for her sister's new flame and Caroline's son considers introducing his new girlfriend to his family.

episodes.name: The Jersey Side Step
episodes.overview: A live music festival courts drama; Caroline's family goes to the Fancy Food Festival in Washington, D.C., but plans to sell water there may go awry after a night of drinking.

episodes.name: Sit Down and Man Up
episodes.overview: Kathy opens a gelato stand in Patterson; Teresa is accused of profiting off her family's recipes; the husbands meet and expose feuds and frail friendships which threaten to jeopardize the Napa trip.

episodes.name: Pack Your Baggage
episodes.overview: The women flee to the California coast to escape Hurricane Irene; tensions between Caroline, Jacqueline and Teresa escalate; Teresa confronts Kathy.

episodes.name: If this RV is a Rockin'
episodes.overview: The housewives decide to try surfing; Caroline has family issues; Jacqueline and Teresa try to see if their friendship can survive.

episodes.name: Whine Country
episodes.overview: The gang's getaway on the west coast continues with a visit to Napa Valley for a business meeting at a vineyard.

episodes.name: Hot Tub of Sour Grapes
episodes.overview: Friendships may be beyond repair when Teresa and Caroline have one last blowout after Caroline overhears a conversation between Teresa and Kathy.

episodes.name: Dinasty of Denial
episodes.overview: New alliances are formed after the trip; Kathy goes to college for a day with her daughter; Teresa invites her ally, Dina, to her Fabellini release party.

episodes.name: A Bald Canary Sings
episodes.overview: Kathy tries to make a business deal while Melissa meets with a music hot-shot; Kim D's annual Porsche Fashion Show; Teresa makes a shocking discovery.

episodes.name: Strip Down Memory Lane
episodes.overview: Melissa prepares to confront her past; a distressing phone call sends Joe Gorga and Rich Wakile to Melissa's rescue; Teresa and Jacqueline's friendship is tested.

episodes.name: Reunion (1)
episodes.overview: The housewives all join together for the first time in over a year to discuss the events of the past season in Part 1 of the Season 4 Reunion.

episodes.name: Reunion (2)

episodes.name: Lost Footage
episodes.overview: The lost footage from Season 4 of The Real Housewives of New Jersey.

episodes.name: Garden State of Emergency
episodes.overview: The wives' holiday homes are in ruins after Hurricane Sandy, Jacqueline faces her son's diagnosis of autism, and Caroline's shocking offer to Joe Gorga could push the wives toward war.

episodes.name: A Manzo of Her Word
episodes.overview: Melissa considers selling her house and moving. Meanwhile, Kathy is tested by her son and her husband; the Lauritas host a poker night; and Caroline and Teresa square off in a fiery exchange.

episodes.name: It's My Party and I'll Fight If I Want To
episodes.overview: Teresa's father goes to the ICU just as the family gears up for a birthday party. Elsewhere, tension grows between Kathy and Teresa; Caroline returns to an unkempt mansion; and a white lie infuriates Teresa.

episodes.name: Gym Rats
episodes.overview: Melissa's past is comes back to haunt her. Kathy hosts a birthday celebration for her daughter and husband. Teresa becomes emotional after she runs into her brother while out.

episodes.name: Everything Is Coming Up Rosie
episodes.overview: Jacqueline meets with the doctor to discuss her son's medical issues. Melissa and Joe fight over rumors Teresa has been saying. Caroline feels that her children are becoming too much like their father.

episodes.name: Drinking With the Enemy
episodes.overview: Rumors about cheating spread. Meanwhile, Teresa plans a healing retreat, where she may have to face Jacqueline, and Kathy attempts to elude all the drama.

episodes.name: When Joes Collide
episodes.overview: The ladies head to Lake George; Teresa prepares to confront Jacqueline; a relationship-building exercise goes awry and threatens to destroy the whole group.

episodes.name: Scum One, Scum All
episodes.overview: Teresa's husband and brother fight; Caroline tries to keep the family together.

episodes.name: On Thin Guid-Ice
episodes.overview: Teresa, her brother and their spouses see a relationship expert; Caroline has a surprising healing agenda.

episodes.name: Best Frenemies Forever
episodes.overview: Tessa and Jacqueline come face to face; Caroline's husband makes a shocking demand; Melissa and Joe get an offer.

episodes.name: Children of the Scorned
episodes.overview: Joe spends time with his goddaughter; Teresa hosts a charity event and confronts Jacqueline; Jacqueline makes an impulsive decision that has her family worried.

episodes.name: Hair-binger of Doom
episodes.overview: An article about Melissa's marriage causes problems; Jacqueline returns from L.A.; Kathy questions her partnership with Rich.

episodes.name: Spaghetti Western & Meatballs
episodes.overview: The ladies go to Arizona to celebrate Melissa's birthday; Jacqueline struggles to mend her relationship with Teresa; Kathy receives a message from another realm.

episodes.name: Horse Whisper to a Scream
episodes.overview: Unorthodox therapy opens old wounds and leaves Caroline in tears; Melissa and Jacqueline face their trust issues; Teresa's husband reveals something shocking.

episodes.name: Zen Things I Hate About You
episodes.overview: A high-wire course is a trust test for Teresa and Melissa; Teresa and Jacqueline grow closer; Caroline and Kathy intervene when tensions boil over between Teresa and her brother.

episodes.name: The Blonde Drops a Bombshell
episodes.overview: Jacqueline faces her fear of public speaking; Caroline debates on selling her family home; an unsettling secret surfaces.

episodes.name: Hair We Go Again
episodes.overview: Caroline's boys open their new restaurant; Melissa goes to Orlando for a live radio performance; Teresa and Jacqueline face their enemies at the opening of their boutique.

episodes.name: Salon, Farewell
episodes.overview: Someone new gets involved in a confrontation, Teresa tries to clear her name, and Kathy, Jacqueline and Caroline focus on their own families.

episodes.name: Reunion (1)
episodes.overview: The ladies look back at the season's most memorable moments, including Melissa and Teresa's feud, and the dramatic trips to Lake George and Arizona.

episodes.name: Reunion (2)
episodes.overview: Teresa and Joe speak about the charges they're faced with; Rosie shares her experience; the ladies discuss the season.

episodes.name: The Real Housewives Tell All (1)
episodes.overview: Never-before-seen footage, from extravagant events to bizarre antics.

episodes.name: The Real Housewives Tell All (2)
episodes.overview: More never-before-seen footage from the season.

episodes.name: What a Difference a Plea Makes
episodes.overview: Teresa and her husband struggle to keep their family together as they enter a public legal battle; Teresa has support from Melissa and Dina; everyone gathers for a party where Amber confronts Melissa.

episodes.name: Oh, Christmas Tre
episodes.overview: Melissa tries to keep traditions alive, Dina feels lonely, Amber becomes consumed with home safety, Teresa Aprea wants her son to join the family restaurant, and Teresa Guidice's legal battles continue.

episodes.name: Trash-Talking
episodes.overview: Joe and Melissa hope to make big money with their new business; Teresa invites friends and family to taste her new recipes for Fabilicious; someone starts a rumor about Nicole.

episodes.name: A Hairy Situation
episodes.overview: Nicole and her boyfriend throw a costume party; Nicole confronts Amber about the rumors.

episodes.name: One Flew Over the Chicken's Nest
episodes.overview: The First Responder's party comes to a dramatic end; Nicole demands loyalty from her boyfriend; Dina still has feelings for her ex; Melissa and Amber discuss the swirling rumor.

episodes.name: The Family Business
episodes.overview: Melissa and Joe try to take their business to the next level; Teresa and Rino want to expand their restaurant business; Rosie introduces her girlfriend; Amber turns to her family for support.

episodes.name: Roses are Red, DNA is Blue
episodes.overview: DIna eats chocolates alone and contemplates divorce; Teresa hunkers down to save her businesses; Melissa tries wooing her husband to spend more time with her.

episodes.name: Guilt Trip
episodes.overview: As news spreads about a possible plea deal in Teresa's case, Dina and Melissa plan a surprise getaway for their friend. Meanwhile, Amber starts texting insults to Nicole's boyfriend, Bobby.

episodes.name: There Will Be Bloodwork
episodes.overview: As their Florida trip approaches, the women cope with monumental life changes; Dina says goodbye to her long-time assistant, Luke; Teresa and her husband face a medical scare; Amber's doctor delivers troubling news.

episodes.name: The Day of Jacqueline
episodes.overview: Dina, Melissa and the twins travel to Florida; Dina has a secret about the twins that threatens to ruin the trip; Amber awaits news about the possible recurrence of her cancer; Jacqueline returns and confronts Teresa about her past.

episodes.name: Gators and Haters
episodes.overview: The tension between Jim, Bobby and Dina comes to a head during the Florida trip; Teresa struggles to figure out how to respond to Jacqueline's text messages; Rosie's love life becomes rocky.

episodes.name: Pack Your Bags and Get Out!
episodes.overview: The shocking rumor about the twins' family is revealed; Teresa and Joe plan a getaway to New York to escape the weight of their legal woes; Chris and Jacqueline try to spice up their relationship.

episodes.name: Sorry, Not Sorry
episodes.overview: A tasting party is planned in the wake of a Florida trip, yet the taste turns sour when some names are left off the guest list. Meanwhile, Dina's Ladybug event approaches; Teresa is pushed to apologize for a rumor; Nicole meets Jacqueline.

episodes.name: Judgement Day
episodes.overview: Rumors swirl and create tension between Teresa and Teresa just as Dina's charity event draws near in the Season 6 finale. Also: Melissa breaks ground on her dream home; and Teresa and Joe Giudice learn their legal fate.

episodes.name: Secrets Revealed (1)
episodes.overview: During a trip to Atlantic City, N.J., the women bare it all, revealing shocking secrets, skimpy clothes and provocative dance moves; Joe Giudice baby-sits Milania; Teresa is offended by Kathy's Christmas gift.

episodes.name: Reunion (1)
episodes.overview: Host Andy Cohen interviews the housewives about the dramatic events that went down during season six; a conversation prompts Teresa Giudice to leave the couch; Dina opens up about where she stands with Caroline, Jacqueline and the others.

episodes.name: Reunion (2)
episodes.overview: Joe Giudice joins his wife to discuss his father's death, his prison sentence and money woes; Joe Gorga defends his relationship with his sister; Jim and Bobby go head to head over everything that happened during season six.

episodes.name: Reunion (3)
episodes.overview: The housewives' reunion ends on an emotional note; Jim faces off against everyone over the rumour spread by Victoria Gotti; Teresa Aprea is not ready to let Teresa Giudice off the hook.

episodes.name: Secrets Revealed (2)
episodes.overview: Dina gathers everyone for some spiritual guidance, but Teresa gets more than she bargained for when her legal issues are called into question; Jim's ex-wife asks Amber to babysit her pet pig; Milania misbehaves.

episodes.name: Teresa Checks In, Part 1: Tre of Life
episodes.overview: The family celebrates its important events for the first time without Teresa. Joe and the girls get help and support from their relatives, including Melissa Gorga and Rosie Pierri. Teresa calls her family and sends daily e-mails.

episodes.name: Teresa Checks In, Part 2: Mr. Mom For Shore
episodes.overview: The family goes on a trip to the Jersey Shore to visit their previous home, possibly for the last time. Joe talks to a friend who has been to a prison. The Giudice family celebrates Independence Day with the Gorgas.

episodes.name: Teresa Checks In, Part 3:  The Visit
episodes.overview: Joe Gorga visits his sister for the first time. Difficult times help the Gorgas and Giudice families to draw closer together. Teresa continues to communicate with her family as much as possible.

episodes.name: Jingle Bells and Prison Cells
episodes.overview: Melissa breaks ground on her new boutique, Envy; Jacqueline hosts a holiday cocktail party; after nearly a year in prison, Teresa returns home to her family just in time for Christmas.

episodes.name: A Very Hairy Christmas
episodes.overview: Melissa hosts a Christmas Eve dinner, during which she reunites with Teresa; Jacqueline gets a surprise call from Teresa as Dolores attempts to reconcile the two former friends; Joe Giudice and Gia are at odds over her New Year's Eve plans.

episodes.name: Leopard Is the New Black
episodes.overview: Jacqueline surprises Teresa by showing up on her doorstep wanting answers; while shopping for her boutique, Melissa hits a roadblock with her opinionated business partner; Siggy throws a leopard-themed birthday party for Dolores.

episodes.name: A Life to Envy
episodes.overview: Melissa's boutique opens, Teresa records her audio book, Jacqueline makes progress on her business venture, plus Dolores and her daughter discuss veterinary school. Later, Siggy and Teresa duel over tabloid gossip.

episodes.name: Dinner Interrupted
episodes.overview: Tensions between Jacqueline and Teresa boil over at a dinner party; Siggy's children confront her with shocking news; Dolores starts a journey toward financial independence; Melissa's children walk in Fashion Week; Teresa and Melissa grow closer.

episodes.name: Swimming With the Gefilte Fishes
episodes.overview: Teresa bids adieu to her ankle bracelet and the ladies plan a trip to celebrate. Also: Siggy reconnects with her religious roots; Dolores makes headway on her home renovation; and Melissa corners Jacqueline about a dust-up with Teresa.
